After a 110 point drop yesterday, the market is set to gap 14 points higher. Normally, a 14 point jump sounds like a lot but in the context of yesterday's action it will only erase some of the closing action for most stocks. Coronavirus worries continue to dominate the headlines while gold continues the selloff that began yesterday morning. $HD earnings and an outsized tech bounce are some of the stories of the morning.
